          <header class="span8 offset1">
            <h1>DevOps Engineer</h1>
            <h2>Tech Development</h2>
          </header>
        </div>

        <div class="row">

          <div id="content" class="span5 offset1 no_masthead">
            <p>THE POSITIVE FUTURE OF COMMUNICATIONS<br>W2O Group is looking for a motivated and skilled Configuration Management Engineer who thrives on automating server launches, stream lining developer workflows and innovating for repeatability in all aspects of the software development life cycle.</p>
<p>As part of the DevOps team you will bring your Chef skills to bear on multiple heterogeneous environments that ranging in complexity from simply LAMP setups to highly intricate big data application topologies. You will work with the build engineer to figure out where the line is between configuration and application. You will work with the development teams to simplify the operation profile of systems. </p>
<p>You are not a BOFH. You are looking for problems. You are documenting issues with applications and looking for ways to contribute meaningfully to the success of customer facing applications. You are working with developers daily to improve the way software is built and deployed. </p>
<p>Duties</p>
<p>Your day to day duties include all of the below. You should be excited, however, by the expectation that any action you take to improve a system configuration or further automate repeating process will benefit the entire engineering team.</p>
<p>* Work with the Director of Operations to refine a DevOps philosophy for the entire company.<br>* Implement that philosophy with various engineering teams using a wide variety of application technologies (PHP, Java, Hadoop, Elasitc Search, Nginx, Apache, Glassfish, Tomcat, MongoDB, MySQL ...)<br>* Remain current and the on the ground expert for the use of Chef by the Operations team.<br>* Work with developers to invite them into cookbook authorship where appropriate.<br>* Embed yourself with an engineering team. Learn their team cadence and culture. Decide how to make the biggest impact on system stability, performance and reliability and act.<br>* Participate in the usual firefighting of the typical system administrators job<br>* Work relentlessly to drive down the number of firefighting incidents with better process, documentation and automation.</p>
<p>Qualification</p>
<p>Do you just know there is a better way that waiting for the next crisis? Have you automated configuraiton management with Chef, then wondered, "Now what?" Are you ready to take your expertise in Chef and realize the power in a broader impact? Ignore the below and apply.</p>
<p>We think the person we are seeking looks like the below. Convince us otherwise -- we're listening.</p>
<p>* 5+ years experience in operations, development, quality assurance or build engineering. <br>* Demonstrable mastery of Chef.<br>* Demonstrable master of the Linux command line (A great story about how you screwed up a production system while gaining this master)<br>* 1+ years in an agile environment (scrum, kanban, etc)<br>* A deep understanding of VCS (git is preferred)<br>* Know something about containers (DockerIO, systemd, etc) then brag about it.<br>* Read the Phoenix Project? Be ready, there will be a quiz (yes really).<br>* You must recognize the social engineering aspect of implementing a DevOps philosphy across multipe heterogeneous teams. Be ready to tell us good stories about your journey to bring Devops</p>
